Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getLatencyFile(25.10)                                    getLatencyFile(25.10)

Name
       getLatencyFile

Syntax
       getLatencyFile

       [-help]

       Returns  the  name of the latency file used by the timing engine. If no
       latency file name is set, getLatencyFile returns nothing,  but  if  you
       have already run skewClock, this command reports the default file name.
       If  you  have  specified  or changed the latency file name by using the
       setLatencyFile command, getLatencyFile reports this name.

       To view the above description in the software, use man getLatencyFile.

